<subSubSection id="C36F21CBFFA6FFD6FC9AF932FBC9FEF3" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCA7240FFA6FFD6FC9AF932FBC9FEF3" blockId="1.[813,1452,1773,1958]" lastBlockId="2.[820,1459,174,358]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA6FFD5FC9AF932FC5AF890" bold="true" box="[813,937,1773,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA6FFD5FC7AF931FB73F893" authorityName="Vari &amp; Melo &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[973,1152,1774,1798]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Protocheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA6FFD5FC7AF931FB73F893" box="[973,1152,1774,1798]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Protocheirodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses the four synapomorphies proposed for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA6FFD5FB64F8D1FA8DF8B3" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1915" box="[1235,1406,1806,1830]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cheirodontinae">Cheirodontinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE40FB1FFA6FFD5FC9AF8F1FC00F8D3" author="Malabarba" box="[813,1011,1838,1862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="193 - 233" refId="ref5103" refString="Malabarba, L. R. 1998. Monophyly of the Cheirodontinae, characters and major clades (Ostariophysi: Characidae). Pp. 193 - 233. In: Malabarba, L. R., R. E. Reis, R. P. Vari, Z. M. S. Lucena &amp; C. A. S. Lucena (Orgs.). Phylogeny and classification of Neotropical fishes. Porto Alegre, Edipucrs." type="book chapter" year="1998">Malabarba (1998)</bibRefCitation>
: 1) the presence of a pseudotympanum, a hiatus in the body wall musculature lateral to at least a portion of the anterior chamber of the swimbladder; 2) the lack of a dark humeral spot; 3) the possession of pedunculate dentition; and 4) the presence of only a single row of regularly arranged premaxillary teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FDEEFF11FCF4FF73" authorityName="Vari &amp; Melo &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[601,775,206,230]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Protocheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FDEEFF11FCF4FF73" box="[601,775,206,230]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Protocheirodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FD9EFF31FD27FE93" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1915" box="[553,724,238,262]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cheirodontinae">Cheirodontinae</taxonomicName>
and indeed members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FE3DFED1FDDEFEB3" box="[394,557,270,294]" class="Actinopterygii" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Characiformes</taxonomicName>
by the unique form of the swimbladder which has a smaller rotund anterior chamber and the posteriorly chamber elaborated into two vertically elongate, side by side, slightly inclined chambers. These modifications yield a unique overall pi (π)-shaped structure (Vari, 1978) (
<figureCitation id="134E6EC5FFA5FFD6FB00FF31FB08FE93" box="[1207,1275,238,262]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[136,175,1504,1528]" captionTargetBox="[136,1459,404,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-108@2.[136,1459,404,1489]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Protocheirodon pi, (A) CAS 41749, 29.5 mm SL; Colombia, Amazonas, Isla de Santa Sofia II, ca. 20 mi (= 32 km) NW of Leticia; (B) live specimen from aquarium without locality information. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo credits: (A) Sandra Raredon (USNM) and (B) Martin and Peter Hoffmann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4974899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4974899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). This trenchant difference 
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FC1AFED0FC07FEB3" box="[941,1012,271,294]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">versus</emphasis>
other cheirodontins is supplemented by a diagnostic combination of meristic, morphometric and details of pigmentation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF0A22C8FFA5FFD6FF3FFA3FFD2DF9AC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4974899" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4974899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4974899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" startId="2.[136,175,1504,1528]" targetBox="[136,1459,404,1489]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BCA7240FFA5FFD6FF3FFA3FFD2DF9AC" blockId="2.[136,1459,1504,1593]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF3FFA3FFF22FA6D" bold="true" box="[136,209,1504,1528]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF6FFA3EFE6CFA6D" box="[216,415,1505,1529]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FF6FFA3EFE70FA6C" authorityName="Vari &amp; Melo &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[216,387,1505,1529]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Protocheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Protocheirodon</taxonomicName>
pi
</emphasis>
, (A) CAS 41749, 29.5 mm SL; Colombia, Amazonas, Isla de Santa Sofia II, 
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FB6DFA3EFB08FA6D" box="[1242,1275,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">ca.</emphasis>
20 mi (= 32 km) NW of Leticia; (B) live specimen from aquarium without locality information. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo credits: (A) Sandra Raredon (USNM) and (B) Martin and Peter Hoffmann.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C36F21CBFFA5FFD6FF3FF9B0FDB0F952" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA7240FFA5FFD6FF3FF9B0FDB0F952" blockId="2.[136,775,1647,1735]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF3FF9B0FEEBF912" bold="true" box="[136,280,1647,1671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Description.</emphasis>
As 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FEF4F9B0FE02F912" authorityName="Vari &amp; Melo &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[323,497,1647,1671]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Protocheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FEF4F9B0FE02F912" box="[323,497,1647,1671]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Protocheirodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus, its description corresponds to the redescription of the typespecies, 
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF51F970FE43F952" box="[230,432,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FF51F970FE67F952" authorityName="Vari &amp; Melo &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[230,404,1711,1735]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Protocheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Protocheirodon</taxonomicName>
pi
</emphasis>
(Vari, 1978).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F21CBFFA5FFD6FF3FF930FF0DF832" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCA7240FFA5FFD6FF3FF930FF0DF832" blockId="2.[136,775,1775,1959]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF3FF930FEFFF892" bold="true" box="[136,268,1775,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FEADF92FFEA4F892" box="[282,343,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Proto</emphasis>
from Greek 
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FE4CF92FFDC7F892" box="[507,564,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">prōto</emphasis>
, meaning first or earliest form of, in reference to the phylogenetic position of the species as sister to all remaining members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FF0EF890FE90F8F2" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1915" box="[185,355,1871,1895]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cheirodontinae">Cheirodontinae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FE19F890FDE8F8F2" box="[430,539,1871,1895]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Cheirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FE19F890FDE8F8F2" box="[430,539,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cheirodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an allusion to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FF64F8B0FEB5F812" box="[211,326,1903,1927]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Cheirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B901AE52FFA5FFD6FF64F8B0FEB5F812" box="[211,326,1903,1927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cheirodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C7509C3FFA5FFD6FE4AF8B0FD5BF812" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1915" box="[509,680,1903,1927]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cheirodontinae">Cheirodontinae</taxonomicName>
. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
